data.name: E_CANNOT_CHANGE_AFTER_INIT
data.value: The code in your application is attempting to set a property of the WebView control that is read-only because the control has already begun initializing. Your code can modify this property before it calls the ISupportInitialize.BeginInit method, but not after.
data.comment: A member has been invoked after the control is already initialized

data.name: E_CLICKONCE_PARTIAL_TRUST
data.value: Unable to initialize a WebView control in a ClickOnce application. See Release notes: https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?linkid=872619
data.comment: ClickOnce uses AppLaunch.exe to host partial-trust applications (and we don't support partial trust)

data.name: E_NOTSUPPORTED_OS_RS4
data.value: Unable to initialize the WebView control because the system is running a version of Windows that doesn’t support this control. The WebView control runs only on Windows 10 April 2018 Update or later.

data.name: E_UNRECOGNIZED_OS
data.value: The system is running a version of Windows that doesn't support this control.
data.comment: OS version check received an OS combination it did not understand

data.name: E_WEBVIEW_ALREADY_INITIALIZED
data.value: The code in your application is attempting to initialize a WebView control that is already initialized.
data.comment: Caller attempted to call BeginInit after calling EndInit

data.name: E_WEBVIEW_ALREADY_INITIALIZING
data.value: The code in your application is attempting to initialize a WebView control that is already in the process of being initialized by a previous call to the ISupportInitialize.BeginInit() method.
data.comment: Caller attempted to call BeginInit after calling BeginInit

data.name: E_WEBVIEW_CANNOT_INVOKE_BEFORE_INIT
data.value: The code in your application is attempting to use a member of the WebView control before the control is completely initialized.
data.comment: A WebView member has been invoked before the control has been initialized

data.name: E_WEBVIEW_INVALID_URI
data.value: The code in your application sets the Source property or calls the Navigate method by using an invalid URI.
data.comment: Navigate called with a value that cannot be converted to Uri

data.name: E_WEBVIEW_NOT_ABSOLUTE_URI
data.value: The code in your application sets the Source property or calls the Navigate method by using a URI that doesn’t have the format of an absolute URI.
data.comment: Source property or Navigate target invoked with a value that is not a proper absolute Uri

data.name: E_WEBVIEW_NOT_INITIALIZED
data.value: The WebView control is not initialized.

data.name: E_WEBVIEW_NOT_INITIALIZING
data.value: Unable to initialize the WebView control because the code in your application calls the IsSupportInitialize.EndInit() method without first calling the ISupportInitialize.BeginInit() method
data.comment: Caller attempted to finalize initialization of the control with EndInit with out requesting it be initialized with BeginInit

data.name: E_WEB_BROWSER_DISABLED
data.value: Unable to initialize the WebView control because the Microsoft Edge web browser has been disabled by the group or location admin policy of your system.
data.comment: Browser disabled by admin local or group policy object

data.name: E_WEB_PERMISSION_RESTRICTED
data.value: Unable to initialize a WebView control in a ClickOnce application or from an application that is opened in certain types of Web browsers. See Release notes: https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?linkid=872619
data.comment: Could be hosted in browser, as an internet zone XBAP, or standalone ClickOnce
